    <body>
        <p class="TableTextSmall">This setting is pre-populated for you during the installation process. </p>
        <p class="TableTextSmall">The site URL is used when it is different from the URL&#160;used during the Pulse configuration. For example, the user may have configured to an IP&#160;address, but now the user is replacing that IP&#160;address with a host name.</p>
        <p class="TableTextSmall">It is important to ensure that the Site URL&#160;exactly matches the DNS entry for your Pulse server. </p>
        <p class="TableTextSmall">The Site&#160;URL&#160;is also included in outbound email notifications.</p>
    </body>
